SGA is submitted

@chrisdutz I've got trouble getting jetty to run since you incorporated the en/de change.
It now looks in the wrong directory.  I tried a couple of variations but wasn't able to get it running. Do you happen to have an idea?

I added

```
#bannerLeft > img {
    height: 200px;
}
```
to the CSS file and it looks better in my opinion. Not great, but better.

@lfrancke  cool, good find:  http://training.apache.org/developers/building.html ... it (mvn site) works.

Hardcoding size in css seems to negate the benefit of SVG (which can scale -- though we do get the transparency).  Though fixed size is likely sufficient.  

I'll play with sizing to make it look even better.  Will close this PR, and start a new/fresh one (I don't know enough, yet, on how to keep modifying this one; open to pointers).
